00:00:00,659 --> 00:00:03,029
Chinese jets get aggressive against South
Korea.

2
00:00:03,029 --> 00:00:05,490
There’s evidence China is killing innocent
people

3
00:00:05,490 --> 00:00:06,490
for their organs.

4
00:00:06,490 --> 00:00:10,720
And a top exec overseeing Google is in the
hot seat.

5
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:12,200
This is China Uncensored.

6
00:00:16,720 --> 00:00:18,980
Welcome to China Uncensored, I’m Chris Chappell.

7
00:00:18,980 --> 00:00:21,269
South Korea is having problems with China,

8
00:00:21,269 --> 00:00:23,890
problems of the military variety.

9
00:00:23,890 --> 00:00:26,490
Chinese military aircraft have been repeatedly
entering

10
00:00:26,490 --> 00:00:28,439
South Korea’s Air Defense Zone.

11
00:00:28,439 --> 00:00:32,710
Now that’s not quite the same as Korean
territorial airspace.

12
00:00:32,710 --> 00:00:35,170
Airspace is covered under the United Nations
Convention

13
00:00:35,170 --> 00:00:37,070
on the Law of the Sea.

14
00:00:37,070 --> 00:00:38,539
Even though this is the air.

15
00:00:38,539 --> 00:00:42,999
It’s defined as 12 nautical miles from a
country’s shoreline.

16
00:00:42,999 --> 00:00:44,629
The Air Defense Zone is bigger

17
00:00:44,629 --> 00:00:46,629
and not defined by treaties.

18
00:00:46,629 --> 00:00:49,430
But still, it’s common practice to notify
a country

19
00:00:49,430 --> 00:00:52,560
if you’re going to fly your planes into
their zone.

20
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:54,070
But the Chinese military didn’t.

21
00:00:54,070 --> 00:00:57,800
In fact, it’s been getting more and more
aggressive.

22
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:00,359
“According to the South Korean Air Force,

23
00:01:00,359 --> 00:01:02,199
the number of Chinese military aircraft

24
00:01:02,199 --> 00:01:05,000
entering its identification zone is rising.

25
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,970
In 2016, there were about 60 incursions,

26
00:01:07,970 --> 00:01:09,670
70 in 2017

27
00:01:09,670 --> 00:01:13,660
and 110 were reported up to September this
year.”

28
00:01:13,660 --> 00:01:15,500
It’s likely the Chinese Communist Party

29
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:19,110
is concerned about a US, South Korea, Japan
alliance,

30
00:01:19,110 --> 00:01:22,410
a sort of Asian NATO, as some have called
it.

31
00:01:22,410 --> 00:01:24,780
In 2016, South Korea and Japan

32
00:01:24,780 --> 00:01:26,200
agreed to an intelligence sharing treaty.

33
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:27,260
China’s military criticized it as part of
a cold war mentality.

34
00:01:27,260 --> 00:01:28,280
Of course, flying your jets through

35
00:01:28,280 --> 00:01:29,840
another country’s air defense zone

36
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:34,090
in no way could be considered a cold war mentality.

37
00:01:34,090 --> 00:01:35,720
Not at all.

38
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:36,900
China is on trial!

39
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:39,450
For some serious crimes against humanity.

40
00:01:39,450 --> 00:01:41,100
Over the weekend in London,

41
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:44,070
an independent people’s tribunal was held
to examine

42
00:01:44,070 --> 00:01:45,790
evidence that the Chinese Communist Party

43
00:01:45,790 --> 00:01:48,410
is killing people for their organs.

44
00:01:48,410 --> 00:01:50,610
People’s tribunals are typically set up

45
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:53,040
by victims of a serious crime,

46
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:56,240
when governments are unwilling to investigate
an issue.

47
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:57,960
After all, what government would want to

48
00:01:57,960 --> 00:02:00,030
offend the Chinese Communist Party?

49
00:02:00,030 --> 00:02:03,060
Do you know how much business we can do in
China?!

50
00:02:03,060 --> 00:02:06,760
“The charges are that many groups including
Falun Gong practitioners,

51
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:09,470
Uighurs, some Christians, and some Buddhists,

52
00:02:09,470 --> 00:02:12,670
have been taken as prisoners, checked on a
regular basis

53
00:02:12,670 --> 00:02:15,190
whether they are medically fit, and then,

54
00:02:15,190 --> 00:02:18,660
when the time comes, their organs are removed.

55
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:21,140
Some stories say without any anesthetics,

56
00:02:21,140 --> 00:02:22,750
in a very horrible way—

57
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:25,890
and immediately transplanted into an organ
visitor.”

58
00:02:25,890 --> 00:02:29,640
Many of the witness who testified were labor
camp survivors.

59
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:33,310
They had stories of extreme torture or sexual
assault—

60
00:02:33,310 --> 00:02:36,350
but also strange medical tests.

61
00:02:36,350 --> 00:02:40,610
Tests very similar to what would be needed
to match an organ.

62
00:02:40,610 --> 00:02:41,890
According to Freedom House,

63
00:02:41,890 --> 00:02:44,390
“The organ transplant industry in China
remains

64
00:02:44,390 --> 00:02:46,600
enormous and growing,

65
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:48,960
even as the number of judicially executed
prisoners

66
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:52,120
has declined over the past decade.”

67
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:54,860
So where are they getting the organs?

68
00:02:54,860 --> 00:02:56,510
The Tribunal’s chair,

69
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:59,730
former English Judge Geoffrey Nice QC,

70
00:02:59,730 --> 00:03:02,260
said the tribunal unanimously found beyond

71
00:03:02,260 --> 00:03:05,040
reasonable doubt that China has been committing

72
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:08,900
forced organ harvesting from prisoners of
conscience.

73
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:10,760
There will be more hearings early next year,

74
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:12,410
followed by a report.

75
00:03:12,410 --> 00:03:13,420
And with any luck,

76
00:03:13,420 --> 00:03:15,220
the issue might start actually getting

77
00:03:15,220 --> 00:03:17,240
some attention from the mainstream media.

78
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:21,850
Of course, I think what they really need as
a publicity stunt.

79
00:03:21,850 --> 00:03:24,350
How about a re-release of The Oregon Trail—

80
00:03:24,350 --> 00:03:26,930
